Apply now Apply now save-icon Job details Salary $60 - $70 an hour Job Type Contract Title: Business Analyst ML and AI Location: San Francisco, CA (Hybrid) Duration: Long Term Skills: Strong hands-on and leadership experience in deploying a board set of AI/ML technologies. Business Systems Analyst. Understanding and experience in ML and data science concepts. Job Description: We are seeking mission-driven, passionate, self-starting, and creative individuals to join our diverse community of smart, fun, wholehearted, and engaged teams. As a Business Systems Analyst in Integrated Informatics, you will work closely with our IT team and our business partners in the area of Commercial, Medical, and Government affairs. These organizations partner across the U.S.’s healthcare systems to deliver ever-better health outcomes for patients while lowering overall healthcare costs. We expect the Business System Analyst to be a trusted partner to our business team with a passion for technology and with proven Business Analyst capabilities. The Business System Analyst must be an effective negotiator, leader, and communicator in working with Rochet their multiple business units as well as with internal IT cross-functional teams. The ideal candidate will be a self-starter with a passion for transforming healthcare, a high level of flexibility, and commitment. This person will share our community values of passion, courage, integrity, and gratitude -- all in service of our mission, “doing now what patients need next. The candidate selected for the position will be part of the Commercial, Data & Insights Product Line under the US Market Domain supporting the following business areas: Data Science & Machine Learning Product: This product "Data Science & Machine Learning" builds and executes on the strategy for Data Science and Machine Learning to further advance our products for patients. This also covers responsibility for platforms such as recommendation engines and the delivery of relevant, timely, and action-oriented insights to field personnel and other channels. Below are some key initiatives under this product: Data Science Workbench for us: Implementation of Advanced Analytical insights and services platform for everyday Commercial AI, systemizing the use of data for exceptional business results and a central solution for the design, deployment, and management of AI applications Natural Language Processing (NLP) Platform: Partnering with external vendor to pilot and deploy in-house built unified NLP platform for training, running, and managing ML models and deploy recommendation applications for field sales force Commercial Data Science (CDS) Sandbox: Pilot and launch web-based, integrated development environment (IDE) that lets you prepare data, build, train, deploy, and monitor your machine in AWS. As a Sr. Business Systems Analyst on the product team, you will: Be a go getter who can wear multiple hats to drive implementation of key data science and ML products initiatives . Have a broad knowledge and leverage the technical capabilities of the internal teams and external technology providers and vendors Collaborate with Product Line Leads, Product Managers, Project Managers/Scrum Masters, Architects, Engineers, Developers, Quality Assurance, and User Experience Designers on scope, solutions, constraints, and risks Analyze/document current and future business and data needs and help translate to the technical teams. Guide and support other Business System Analyst as they develop the detailed requirements (stories) Perform knowledge transfer to training and communication teams and support user deployment activities as needed Produce detailed wireframes and mockups using visualization tools for prototyping Requirements: Bachelor’s degree in Business, Information Systems or related field; Master's degree in Business or Science is preferred Overall 7+ years of experience as Business Systems Analyst Strong hands-on and leadership experience in deploying a board set of AI/ML technologies Experience and understanding of application development methodology - including Agile and Waterfall approaches, functional requirements, process modeling/re-engineering, use case development, user acceptance testing, organizational change management, and large-scale system implementations Understanding and experience in ML and data science concepts Demonstrated success in handling initiatives of high complexity, high profile, and large-scale programs Demonstrated ability to quickly learn the business in unfamiliar areas Ability to work in an environment of competing and alternating priorities with a constant focus on delivery Excellent communication (written and oral) and presentation skills; solid business acumen; well-honed influencing skills are essential Self-motivated and team-oriented; able to work both autonomously and effectively as part of a geographically dispersed team Experience with Jira, Confluence, and other Agile tools preferred Proven leadership abilities and emotional intelligence Job Type: Contract Pay: $60.00 - $70.00 per hour Compensation package: Overtime pay Experience level: 7 years Schedule: Monday to Friday Ability to commute/relocate: South San Francisco, CA 94080: Reliably commute or planning to relocate before starting work (Required) Application Question(s): Years of experience As a Business Analyst: Years of experience in deploying a board set of AI/ML Technologies: Years of experience in ML and Data Science Concepts: Years of experience and understanding of Application Development Methodology - Including Agile and Waterfall approaches, Functional Requirements, Process Modeling/Re-Engineering, use case Development, User Acceptance Testing, Organizational Change Management, and Large-Scale System Implementations: Years of experience with Jira, Confluence, and other Agile Tools: Work Location: In person Speak with the employer +91 7139997366 If you require alternative methods of application or screening, you must approach the employer directly to request this as Indeed is not responsible for the employer's application process.

Cloud Database Migration Specialist - job post Apptrics LLC San Francisco, CA $75 - $85 an hour -  Contract Apply now Apply now save-icon Job details Salary $75 - $85 an hour Job Type Contract Cloud Database Migration Specialist Locations – Onsite in SFO,CA ( Client office) Duration : Long term Job Summary: We are seeking a highly skilled Cloud Database Migration Specialist to manage the migration of large-scale databases from Oracle Exadata and SQL Server to AWS RDS Database. The ideal candidate will have extensive experience with cloud database migration, specifically with Oracle Exadata and SQL Server databases, and will be responsible for ensuring a seamless transition of terabytes of data to AWS RDS. Key Responsibilities: Manage the end-to-end process of migrating Oracle Exadata and SQL Server databases to AWS RDS, ensuring minimal downtime and data loss. Develop and execute detailed migration plans, including data migration, database schema migration, and application migration. Configure and optimize AWS RDS databases to ensure optimal performance and scalability. Work closely with internal stakeholders and external vendors to ensure a smooth migration process and timely resolution of any issues. Monitor and troubleshoot migrated databases to ensure that they are running smoothly and meeting performance targets. Create and maintain documentation related to the migration process, including migration plans, migration runbooks, and database configuration guides. Stay current with new AWS services and features related to cloud database migration and incorporate them into migration plans as appropriate. Qualifications: Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or related field. 5+ years of experience in database administration, with a focus on cloud database migration. Extensive experience migrating Oracle Exadata and SQL Server databases to AWS RDS, including experience with terabytes of data. Experience with database replication and backup/restore strategies in a cloud environment. Knowledge of AWS services such as AWS Database Migration Service (DMS), AWS Schema Conversion Tool (SCT), and AWS CloudFormation. Strong understanding of database design, database security, and database performance optimization. Excellent problem-solving skills and ability to troubleshoot complex technical issues. Strong verbal and written communication skills, with the ability to communicate technical information to non-technical stakeholders. Preferred Qualifications: AWS Certification in Database Specialty or Solutions Architect. Experience with other cloud database migration tools and platforms. Experience with NoSQL databases such as DynamoDB.
